  "response": "Here are some strategies to help you avoid silly mistakes in tests:\n\n1. Read carefully\n- Read each question thoroughly\n- Pay attention to details and keywords\n- Underline/circle important information\n\n2. Slow down and be methodical\n- Don't rush\n- Work at a steady, controlled pace\n- Take deep breaths if you feel anxious\n\n3. Double-check your work\n- Review each answer before moving to the next\n- Check calculations and work\n- Look for obvious errors\n\n4. Practice test-taking techniques\n- Do practice tests under timed conditions\n- Learn from past mistakes\n- Develop a consistent approach\n\n5. Manage test anxiety\n- Get enough sleep before the test\n- Eat a good meal\n- Use relaxation techniques\n\n6. Common mistake prevention\n- Watch for:\n  * Sign errors\n  * Decimal point placement\n  * Unit conversions\n  * Negatives/positives\n  * Copying numbers incorrectly\n\n7. Use test strategy\n- Answer easier questions first\n- Mark questions you're unsure about\n- Use all available time to review\n\n8. Stay focused\n- Minimize distractions\n- Maintain concentration\n- Avoid mind-wandering\n\n9. Create a checklist\n- Make a personal error-checking routine\n- Develop habits to catch common mistakes\n\nRemember: Consistent practice and self-awareness are key!",
